				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Num=
bers significantly larger than those used regularly</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For other us=
es, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Large_number_(disambiguati=
on)" class=3D"mw-disambig" title=3D"Large number (disambiguation)">Large nu=
mber (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p><b>Large numbers</b> are numbers far larger than those encountered in ev=
eryday life, such as simple counting or financial transactions. These quant=
ities appear prominently in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathem=
atics" title=3D"Mathematics">mathematics</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Physical_cosmology" title=3D"Physical cosmology">cosmology</a>,=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography" title=3D"Cryptograp=
hy">cryptography</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statisti=
cal_mechanics" title=3D"Statistical mechanics">statistical mechanics</a>.  =
<b>Googology</b> studies the naming conventions and properties of these imm=
ense numbers.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Large_numbers#cite_note-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Large_n=
umbers#cite_note-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Since the customary <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decimal=
" title=3D"Decimal">decimal</a> format of large numbers can be lengthy, oth=
er systems have been devised that allows for shorter representation. For ex=
ample, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billion" title=3D"Billion=
">billion</a> is represented as 13 characters (1,000,000,000) in decimal fo=
rmat, but is only 3 characters (10<sup>9</sup>) when expressed in <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation" title=3D"Exponentiation">=
exponential format</a>. A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trillion=
" title=3D"Trillion">trillion</a> is 17 characters in decimal, but only 4 (=
10<sup>12</sup>) in exponential. Values that vary dramatically can be repre=
sented and compared <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphics" titl=
e=3D"Graphics">graphically</a> via <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Logarithmic_scale" title=3D"Logarithmic scale">logarithmic scale</a>.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Natural_language_numbering"=
>Natural language numbering</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/i=
ndex.php?title=3DLarge_numbers&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"=
Edit section: Natural language numbering"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Names_of_large_numbe=
rs" title=3D"Names of large numbers">Names of large numbers</a></div>
<p>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_language" title=3D"Na=
tural language">natural language</a> numbering system represents large numb=
ers using names rather than a series of digits. For example "billion" may b=
e easier to comprehend for some readers than "1,000,000,000". Sometimes it =
is shortened by using a suffix, for example 2,340,000,000 =3D 2.34 B (B =3D=
 billion). A numeric value can be lengthy when expressed in words, for exam=
ple, "2,345,789" is "two million, three hundred forty five thousand, seven =
hundred and eighty nine".
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Scientific_notation">Scient=
ific notation</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DLarge_numbers&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: =
Scientific notation"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bra=
cket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_notation" title=3D"S=
cientific notation">Scientific notation</a> was devised to represent the va=
st range of values encountered in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Scientific_research" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Scientific research">sc=
ientific research</a> in a format that is more compact than traditional for=
mats yet allows for high precision when called for. A value is represented =
as a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decimal_fraction" class=3D"mw=
-redirect" title=3D"Decimal fraction">decimal fraction</a> <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplication" title=3D"Multiplication">times</a>=
 a multiple <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_of_10" title=3D"=
Power of 10">power of 10</a>. The factor is intended to make reading compre=
hension easier than a lengthy series of zeros. For example, 1.0<span style=
=3D"margin:0 .15em 0 .25em">=C3=97</span>10<sup><span class=3D"nowrap"><spa=
n data-sort-value=3D"7000900000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>9</span></sup> ex=
presses one billion =E2=80=93 1 followed by nine zeros. The <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplicative_inverse" title=3D"Multiplicative i=
nverse">reciprocal</a>, one billionth, is 1.0<span style=3D"margin:0 .15em =
0 .25em">=C3=97</span>10<sup><span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=
=3D"2999100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>=E2=88=929</span></sup>. Sometimes=
 the letter <i>e</i> replaces the exponent, for example 1 billion may be ex=
pressed as 1e9 instead of 1.0<span style=3D"margin:0 .15em 0 .25em">=C3=97<=
/span>10<sup><span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"70009000000000=
00000=E2=99=A0"></span>9</span></sup>.
</p>
