<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Accuracy">Accuracy</h2><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLarge_numbers&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: Accuracy"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>For a number <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><s=
pan class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display:=
 none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\dis=
playstyle 10^{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{n}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/eeff06a7c9ad9455cb809047cfc97a92c51e1bf7" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:3.543ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 10^=
{n}}"></span>, one unit change in <i>n</i> changes the result by a factor 1=
0. In a number like <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline=
"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"disp=
lay: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{=
\displaystyle 10^{\,\!6.2\times 10^{3}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
            <mspace width=3D"negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
            <mn>6.2</mn>
            <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
            <msup>
              <mn>10</mn>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>3</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{\,\!6.2\t=
imes 10^{3}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/09630ecaf14e1d8798974dd334d86b1806d69ea1" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:8.413ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 10^=
{\,\!6.2\times 10^{3}}}"></span>, with the 6.2 the result of proper roundin=
g using significant figures, the true value of the exponent may be 50 less =
or 50 more. Hence the result may be a factor <span class=3D"mwe-math-elemen=
t mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-m=
athml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/=
Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle 10^{50}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>50</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{50}}</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6f32ecb7973f19a8ebafcdc5b850eb4c66611d72" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:4.201ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 10^=
{50}}"></span> too large or too small. This seems like extremely poor accur=
acy, but for such a large number it may be considered fair (a large error i=
n a large number may be "relatively small" and therefore acceptable).
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"For_very_large_numbers">For=
 very large numbers</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?=
title=3DLarge_numbers&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit sec=
tion: For very large numbers"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In the case of an approximation of an extremely large number, the <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relative_error" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Relative error">relative error</a> may be large, yet there may still=
 be a sense in which one wants to consider the numbers as "close in magnitu=
de". For example, consider
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 10^{10}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
