            </msup>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{10^{9}}}<=
/annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/af10c2aa9f44f255b26e6806cff77e649827a12d" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:5.033ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 10^=
{10^{9}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>to be "close in magnitude". The relative error between these two numbers=
 is large, and the relative error between their logarithms is still large; =
however, the relative error in their second-iterated logarithms is small:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \log _{10}(\log _{10}(10^{10^{10}}))=3D10}">
