</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/06474866d0f840be3487dfab86ae90886aaaf614" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:5.397ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle f_{=
0}(n)}"></span> (<i>n</i>=E2=89=A51), it is possible to produce a faster-gr=
owing sequence <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><sp=
an class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: =
none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\disp=
laystyle f_{1}(n)=3Df_{0}^{n}(n)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>f</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msubsup>
          <mi>f</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
