        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle f_{1}(n)=3Df_=
{0}^{n}(n)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/9faf946171a4d8a1e7a21fc264c7885b48173eee" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.005ex; width:14.239ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle f_=
{1}(n)=3Df_{0}^{n}(n)}"></span> (where the superscript <i>n</i> denotes the=
 <i>n</i><sup>th</sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Functional_=
power" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Functional power">functional power</a=
>). This can be repeated any number of times by letting <span class=3D"mwe-=
math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline=
 mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w=
3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle f_{k}(n)=3Df_{k-1}^{n}(n)=
}">
